rench form of   Damian  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Damian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Francisco, Juan, Jose, Pedro, Alberto, Armando, Carlos, Cesar, Elena, Felipe, Lourdes, Luis.","Spanish (<b>Damián</b>), German, Romanian, Italian, and Polish: from the personal name <i>Damián</i>, <i>Damian</i> respectively, Greek <i>Damianos</i> (from <i>damazein</i> ‘to subdue’), Latin <i>Damianus</i>. Saint Damian was an early Christian saint martyred in Cilicia in  AD  303 under the emperor Domitian, together with his brother Cosmas (see   Kosmas  ). In some accounts the brothers are said to have been doctors, and together they were regarded as the patrons of physicians and apothecaries. A later Saint Damian lived in the 7th–8th centuries and was bishop of Pavia; he may have had some influence on the popularity of the personal name in Italy. This surname is also found among Rusyns (Lemkos).","In some cases probably also French (southern France and Lorraine): from a variant of the personal name   Damien  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Valois","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Henri, Normand, Alcide, Armand, Emilien, Gilberte, Gilles, Herve, Jacques, Lucien.","French:","habitational name from (Le) Valois, the name of a few places in France, e.g. in Forez and Limousin."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Drogon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Norman origin but uncertain meaning and derivation. Norman given names are most often of Continental Germanic derivation, and this one is possibly ultimately from Old Saxon <i>drog</i> ‘ghost, phantom’, or perhaps from Old High German <i>tragen</i> ‘to carry’. However, most plausible is the suggestion that it was brought into Germanic from Slavic as a short form of a name formed with <i>dorogo</i> ‘dear’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Drogon D'Amiens Valois was born in 1020, in Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France. He married Adèle de Corbie in 1045, in Corbie, Somme, Picardie, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1069, in Valois, Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, France, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1020–1069":"1020–1069","1010–1089":"1010–1089","1030–1066":"1030–1066","1069":"1069","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1066":"1066","3 March 1066":"3. märts 1066","1010":"1010","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Corbie, Somme, Picardie, France":"Corbie, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, France":"Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Valois, Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, France":"Valois, Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1020–1069":"1020–1069","1010–1089":"1010–1089","1030–1066":"1030–1066","1069":"1069","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1066":"1066","3 March 1066":"3. maaliskuuta 1066","1010":"1010","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Corbie, Somme, Picardie, France":"Corbie, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, France":"Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, Ranska","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Valois, Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, France":"Valois, Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, Ranska"},"fr":{"1020–1069":"1020–1069","1010–1089":"1010–1089","1030–1066":"1030–1066","1069":"1069","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1066":"1066","3 March 1066":"3 mars 1066","1010":"1010","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France","Corbie, Somme, Picardie, France":"Corbie, Somme, Picardie, France","Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, France":"Abbeville-Saint-Lucien, Oise, Picardie, France","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-Fran